Class HttpResponseHeader

      • HttpResponseHeader

        public HttpResponseHeader(HttpRequestHeader requestHeader,
                  java.io.BufferedInputStream bIn,
                  int executionStep,
                  CookieHandler cookieHandler,
                  java.lang.Object logVectorObject)
                   throws java.io.IOException
        Reads the response header from a buffered input stream.
        Parameters:
        requestHeader - reference to request header (can be null if cookies are not supported)
        bIn - buffered input stream from which the response header is read
        executionStep - current execution step of caller (any value is ok)
        cookieHandler - reference to cookie handler (can be null if cookies are not supported)
        logVectorObject - reference to log vector (can be null if no log is needed)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
